trans-unit.source: Provides standard facilities for creating and managing a type-safe, ordered collection of <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroup"></xref> objects.
This collection supports standard zero-based indexing.
The <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table.RowGroups%2A> property provided by the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.Table> class returns a <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection>.
For more information, see [How to: Manipulate a Table's Row Groups through the RowGroups Property](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/how-to-manipulate-table-row-groups-through-the-rowgroups-property.md).
Appends a specified item to the collection.
An item to append to the collection.
Raised when *item* already belongs to a collection.
Raised when *item* is **null**.
Gets or sets the pre-allocated collection item capacity for this collection.

The <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> property represents the number of pre-allocated slots for storing items in this collection, whereas the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count%2A> property represents the actual number of items currently in the collection.
The value of <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> is always at least as large as the value of <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count%2A>.
When newly added collection items cause the collection count to exceed the collection capacity, the capacity is automatically increased to accommodate the newly added collection items.
Increasing the collection capacity involves allocating additional collection slots, which incurs both performance and memory overhead.

Use the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> property to optimize the collection capacity in cases where the total or maximum number of collection items is known in advance.
Use the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.TrimToSize%2A> method to cause the collection capacity to equalized with the current collection count.
The pre-allocated collection item capacity for this collection.
The default value is **8**.

Raised when an attempt is made to set <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCellCollection.Capacity"></xref> to a value that is less than the current value of <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableCellCollection.Count"></xref>.
Clears all items from the collection.

After calling <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Clear%2A>, the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count%2A> property becomes **0** and the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> property is unchanged.

To set a new capacity, call <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.TrimToSize%2A> or explicitly set a new capacity through the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> property.
Queries for the presence of a specified item in the collection.
An item to query for the presence of in the collection.
**true** if the specified *item* is present in the collection; otherwise, **false**.
Copies the contents of the collection and inserts them into a specified array starting at a specified index position in the array.
A one-dimensional array to which the collection contents will be copied.
This array must use zero-based indexing.
A zero-based index in array specifying the position at which to begin inserting the copied collection objects.

Raised when *array* includes items that are not compatible with the type <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroup"></xref>, or if *arrayIndex* specifies a position that falls outside of the bounds of *array*.
Raised when *array* is **null**.
Raised when *arrayIndex* is less than **0**.
Copies the contents of the collection and inserts them into a specified <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroup"></xref> array of starting at a specified index position in the array.

The <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> property represents the number of pre-allocated slots for storing items in this collection, whereas the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count%2A> property represents the actual number of items currently in the collection.
The value of <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> is always at least as large as the value of <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count%2A>.
When newly added collection items cause the collection count to exceed the collection capacity, the capacity is automatically increased to accommodate the newly added collection items.
Increasing the collection capacity involves allocating additional collection slots, which incurs both performance and memory overhead.

Use the <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.TrimToSize%2A> method to cause the collection capacity to equalized with the current collection count.
The number of items currently contained by the collection.
Returns the zero-based index of specified collection item.

The zero-based index of the specified collection item, or **-1** if the specified item is not a member of the collection.
Inserts a specified item in the collection at a specified index position.

If <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count%2A> equals <xref:System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity%2A> for this collection, the collection capacity automatically is increased before the new item is inserted.

Optimizes memory consumption for the collection by setting the underlying collection <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Capacity"></xref> equal to the <xref href="System.Windows.Documents.TableRowGroupCollection.Count"></xref> of items currently in the collection.
This method can be used to minimize memory overhead for a collection, particularly if the set of items contained by the collection is expected to be static.
